cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.DS 

This paper deals with learning a kernel matrix from relative comparison human feedback, which is a problem commonly encountered in machine learning and information retrieval. The paper proposes a novel framework for efficiently learning the similarity of a large set of objects in an online manner, which is relevant to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), information retrieval (cs.IR), computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
